<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/66> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #66" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 2.28.1; Dion. Hal. 6.34.1, and 69.3, on Verginius; Ascon. 76 C, with reading L. Veturius; Chr. 354 (Caelimontano et Cicurino); Fast. Hyd. (Caelimontano II et Vitellino III); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 88, 352f. In this, the year of the first secession of the Plebs, a conciliatory Dictator (see below) induced them to serve against invaders. Veturius fought the Aequi and Verginius the Volscians (Liv. 2.30.8-15; Dion.{14} Hal. 6.42.1-2; Frontin. Str. 2.1.7). On Verginius, see Lübker no. 7, and on Veturius, ib. no. 4." .
